.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "Apr 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-completion-zsh - Generate the autocompletion script for zsh


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira completion zsh [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate the autocompletion script for the zsh shell.

.PP
If shell completion is not already enabled in your environment you will need
to enable it.  You can execute the following once:

.EX
echo "autoload -U compinit; compinit" >> ~/.zshrc
.EE

.PP
To load completions in your current shell session:

.EX
source <(openpass completion zsh)
.EE

.PP
To load completions for every new session, execute once:

.SS Linux:
.EX
symaira completion zsh > "${fpath[1]}/_openpass"
.EE

.SS macOS:
.EX
symaira completion zsh > $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh/site-functions/_openpass
.EE

.PP
You will need to start a new shell for this setup to take effect.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for zsh

.PP
\fB--no-descriptions\fP[=false]
	disable completion descriptions


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsymaira-completion(1)\fP
